OL,3,CAt least 172 mothers killed by sons in
OL,4,Cpast 15 years, report reveals
OL,6,FThe soon-to-be-released report has
OL,7,Fhighlighted a disturbing rise in
OL,8,Fmatricide, in an effort that the
OL,9,Ffindings will push the government to
OL,10,Fintroduce a clear strategy to tackle
OL,11,Ffatal violence against women.
OL,13,FThe organisation findings reveal that
OL,14,Fmental health played a role in most
OL,15,Fmatricides, with 58% of cases (102)
OL,16,Flinked to mental health issues.
