OL,6,F"Nobody is looking at the bigger
OL,7,Fpicture to say this is happening all
OL,8,Fthe time. It's such a constant trend
OL,9,Fyear by year, the numbers don't change
OL,10,Fthat much."
OL,12,FIn 113 matricide cases, there was
OL,13,Fevidence the victim was "overkilled" -
OL,14,Fsubjected to "excessive, brutal
OL,15,Fviolence" beyond what was needed to
OL,16,Fcause death, often involving multiple
OL,17,Fmethods of killing.
OL,19,FIn one case, 76-year-old Bhajan Kaur
OL,20,Fwas murdered by her son, Sundeep
OL,21,FSingh, 48.
