OL,3,CAt least 172 mothers killed by sons in
OL,4,Cpast 15 years, report reveals
OL,6,FMeanwhile, 37 women were killed
OL,7,Falongside 53 children, most often by
OL,8,Fthe children's father in 77% of cases.
OL,10,FA bleak picture
OL,12,FThe report analysis reveals that one
OL,13,Fwoman has been killed every three days
OL,14,Fin the UK since 2009.
OL,16,FIt shows that 90% of the killers were
OL,17,Ffamily members, partners, or known to
OL,18,Fthe victim, with 61% being current or
OL,19,Fformer partners. Around 80% of the
OL,20,Fkillings occurred in the victim's or
OL,21,Fperpetrator's home.
