OL,3,CAt least 172 mothers killed by sons in
OL,4,Cpast 15 years, report reveals
OL,6,FThe authors argue that "manslaughter
OL,7,Fis a controversial crime," as of the
OL,8,F229 men convicted of manslaughter
OL,9,Fbefore 2020, only 18 remain in custody.
OL,11,FSome men avoided prison altogether.
OL,12,FOne example cited in the report
OL,13,Finvolves a man who slit his wife's
OL,14,Fthroat from behind.
OL,16,FDespite a pathologist's suggestion of
OL,17,Fmurder, he claimed self-defence, and
OL,18,Fthe court accepted this, allowing him
OL,19,Fto walk free.
